snippet.textDisplay:
i think Ransom DID do something to Marta’s car. set it up so he could be the savior and immediately endear himself to her as her ally and friend who wants to help.
—During the will reading scene, you see that Ransom leaves early (before it’s even fully read). doesn’t make a big show of it, but he leaves right as the family start freaking out on the attorney, and knowing his family he knew their wrath would then turn to marta. so it was perfect.
—also, since he left a short while before marta even got to her car, there’s no reason he would’ve still been on the property and therefore shouldn’t have been there at the exact same time that she was leaving.
he planned it all out, wanting to be by her side while waiting for Blanc to figure out/expose her, and also in case any issues arose so that he could be able to fix them.

snippet.textDisplay:
Disclaimer: I talk about the craziness so if you wish an opportunity to think about it less than is possible today, I recommend stopping now.

Is YouTube itself encouraging shying away from naming *the craziness*? I remember seeing something to that effect, possibly something to do with curbing misinformation, but I could very well be wrong. It seems like a poor choice to me, allowing more gravitas to gather around the name than would normally. I think it should be given the power and the respect proportionate to its importance, yes, but no more. Let's not make it any spookier than a microscopic, nigh-invisible enemy with the capacity to kill our loved ones already is.

At the end of the day, though, I'm just some guy spouting opinions onto the internet under a quite unrelated video. Have a good day, dear reader, and I apologize if I've added any stress to it.

snippet.textDisplay: I don’t think it’s about staying in the middle of the road politically. It might just be because I’m as sleep deprived as I’ll ever be, but what if they [CinemaWins/Sins crew] analyzed everything great and wrong with music videos or songs? I know M/V’s are short, but, heck, they could do entire albums at a time or go really in depth on anything to be said. I know, I’m crazy, but it would be really interesting to see them going into their thoughts on overall tone of a song, cool sets in M/V’s, choreography and translations (when they apply), and maybe even stating their belief of what the lyrics or symbolisms in the videos mean. Heck, I already know that at least some of the crew are really in love with music [see how much they talk about scores] and facial expression.
(please don’t bash on me, I know I’m insane)

Just watched this film last night. I enjoyed it except for 2 things;
1) Craig's voice was unnecessary and annoying. I don't know why some directors want to do this. It's like Sam Jackson in Kingsman.
2) I'm not a CSI, but Harlan killed himself probably 20 feet away from Marta. I don't believe blood flies that far. Maybe I'm wrong. If it does, why wasn't there blood anywhere else in the room besides where he died. I just didn't like it.
Other than that, it was a good, fun film.
